OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1784679493
OL,3,CWhat countries are planning to ban
OL,4,Csocial media for under-16s?
OL,6,FSo what countries are looking to copy
OL,7,FAustralia and France, and how will
OL,8,Fthey implement their own bans? ITV
OL,9,FNews explains.
OL,11,FGreek Prime Minister Kyriakos
OL,12,FMitsotakis announced plans for a total
OL,13,Fsocial media ban for children 15 and
OL,14,Funder on April 8, making it the latest
OL,15,FEuropean country to follow in
OL,16,FAustralia's footsteps.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/24
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1784679493
OL,3,CWhat countries are planning to ban
OL,4,Csocial media for under-16s?
OL,6,FThe new law targets social media
OL,7,Fplatforms and puts the onus on them to
OL,8,Fprevent children from keeping or
OL,9,Fmaking user profiles. Penalties for
OL,10,Ffailing to comply include fines of up
OL,11,Fto 6% of the company's global turnover
OL,12,For restrictions on operations.
OL,14,FMitsotakis said the move was to tackle
OL,15,Fsocial media addiction and anxieties
OL,16,Fin children, and to protect them from
OL,17,Fharm.
OL,19,FThe law is expected to be introduced
OL,20,Fthis summer and will come into force
OL,21,Ffrom January 1 next year.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/24
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
