OL,3,CWhat countries are planning to ban
OL,4,Csocial media for under-16s?
OL,6,FAustria's coalition government
OL,7,Fannounced plans to ban social media
OL,8,Fuse for children under 14 in late
OL,9,FMarch.
OL,11,FIt is not yet clear how the ban will
OL,12,Fwork or when it will be imposed, with
OL,13,Fdraft legislation expected to be
OL,14,Ffinalised this summer. It will also
OL,15,Frequire parliamentary approval.
OL,17,FVice Chancellor Andreas Babler said
OL,18,Fthe government would no longer "look
OL,19,Fon" as social media platforms "make
OL,20,Four children addicted and often also
OL,21,Fsick".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/24
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
